OL,3,CAir fryers causing tens of thousands
OL,4,Cof pounds worth of damage, says insurer
OL,6,FLuke Osborne, deputy technical
OL,7,Fdirector at charity Electrical Safety
OL,8,FFirst, said that while air fryers have
OL,9,F"become a staple part of our kitchen
OL,10,Fset-up" there is a risk of accidents
OL,11,Fif people do not ensure they are using
OL,12,Fthem safely.
OL,14,FHe said: "Always register the product
OL,15,Fto make sure you are contactable in
OL,16,Fthe event a fault is detected by the
OL,17,Fmanufacturer. Never overfill your air
OL,18,Ffryer and never plug the appliance
OL,19,Finto an extension lead to avoid
OL,20,Fpotential overheating.
